  "prompt": "What are the major events that happened in 1997?",
  "response": "1997 was a significant year marked by pivotal events across various domains, including politics, science, technology, culture, and the economy. Here's an overview of some of the major happenings from that year:\n\n### **Political and International Events**\n\n1. **Handover of Hong Kong (July 1, 1997):**\n   - The United Kingdom officially transferred sovereignty of Hong Kong to the People's Republic of China, ending 156 years of British colonial rule. This event was governed by the Sino-British Joint Declaration, which outlined the \"one country, two systems\" principle, allowing Hong Kong a high degree of autonomy for 50 years after the handover.\n\n2. **Death of Princess Diana (August 31, 1997):**\n   - Diana, Princess of Wales, died in a car crash in Paris. Her tragic and untimely death led to an unprecedented global outpouring of grief and had a profound impact on the British royal family and public discourse around privacy and the media.\n\n3. **Rise of Tony Blair and the Labour Party (May 2, 1997):**\n   - The Labour Party, under the leadership of Tony Blair, won a landslide victory in the United Kingdom general elections, ending 18 years of Conservative government. This ushered in the \"New Labour\" era, characterized by centrist policies and modernization of the party.\n\n4. **Adoption of the Kyoto Protocol (December 11, 1997):**\n   - An international treaty adopted in Kyoto, Japan, aimed at reducing greenhouse gas emissions to combat global warming. It was a significant step in global environmental policy, setting binding emission reduction targets for developed countries.\n\n### **Science and Technology**\n\n1. **IBM's Deep Blue Defeats Garry Kasparov (May 11, 1997):**\n   - IBM's chess-playing computer Deep Blue made history by defeating the reigning world chess champion, Garry Kasparov, in a six-game match. This event marked a milestone in artificial intelligence and computer science.\n\n2. **Mars Pathfinder Mission (July 4, 1997):**\n   - NASA's Mars Pathfinder successfully landed on Mars, deploying the Sojourner rover. The mission provided valuable data about Mars' geology and atmosphere and demonstrated new technologies for planetary exploration.\n\n3. **First Steps Toward Human Genome Project Completion:**\n   - Significant progress was made in mapping the human genome, laying the groundwork for advancements in genetics, medicine, and biotechnology.\n\n### **Economic Events**\n\n1. **Asian Financial Crisis Beginnings (July 1997):**\n   - Triggered by the collapse of the Thai baht after the government was forced to float it due to lack of foreign currency to support its fixed exchange rate, the crisis rapidly spread to other Asian economies. It led to severe economic downturns, currency devaluations, and financial instability across the region.\n\n### **Cultural Highlights**\n\n1. **Publication of \"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone\" (June 26, 1997):**\n   - J.K. Rowling's first book in the Harry Potter series was published in the United Kingdom. The series would go on to become a global phenomenon, profoundly influencing literature and popular culture.\n\n2. **Release of Blockbuster Films:**\n   - **\"Titanic\"**: Although it premiered in December 1997, James Cameron's epic romance-disaster film became one of the highest-grossing films of all time, winning numerous awards and becoming a cultural touchstone.\n   - **\"Men in Black\"** and **\"The Fifth Element\"** also debuted, contributing to the year's vibrant film landscape.\n\n3. **Debut of \"South Park\" (August 13, 1997):**\n   - The animated television series \"South Park\" premiered on Comedy Central, known for its irreverent humor and social satire, and it quickly became a staple of American television.\n\n4. **Music and Entertainment:**\n   - The late 1990s saw the rise of pop groups like the Spice Girls, who debuted in 1997 with hits like \"Wannabe,\" promoting themes of \"girl power\" and becoming icons of the decade.\n\n### **Sports**\n\n1. **Tiger Woods' Early Years:**\n   - While Tiger Woods turned professional in 1996, 1997 was a formative year in his career, setting the stage for his future dominance in golf.\n\n2. **Atlanta Braves' World Series Victory:**\n   - The Atlanta Braves won the 1997 World Series, their first championship since moving to Atlanta, solidifying their status as a dominant team in Major League Baseball during the 1990s.\n\n### **Miscellaneous**\n\n1. **Maker International and Technological Advances:**\n   - Continued advancements in the internet and mobile technology laid the groundwork for the digital revolution that would accelerate in the following years.\n\n2. **Environmental Milestones:**\n   - Growing awareness and initiatives related to climate change and conservation, partially spurred by the Kyoto Protocol, influenced global policies and public opinion.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nThe year 1997 was marked by transformative events that had lasting impacts on international relations, technology, culture, and the global economy. From historic political shifts and groundbreaking technological achievements to cultural phenomena that continue to influence society today, 1997 remains a noteworthy year in recent history.",
